objects.text:
PEACE IS A LIE, THERE IS ONLY
PASSION

THROUGH PASSION, I GAIN
STRENGTH

THROUGH STRENGTH, I GAIN
POWER

THROUGH POWER, I GAIN
VICTORY

THROUGH VICTORY,
MY CHAINS ARE BROKEN

rows.title: WHEN YOUR PATHS CROSSED...
rows.titleText:
The memory of the first encounter with your Master is still fresh in your mind. You remember it as if it were yesterday. The way they looked at you. The spark of interest that flashed through their eyes. The potential they instantly perceived in you.... 

Pick a Location and a Context.

objects.title: THE BAZAAR
objects.text: It was one of those noisy and smoky souks that flourish on the most squalid planets, whose atmosphere is saturated with the smell of spices and drugs. They was walking around like a tourist, amidst the cacophony of beasts, merchants and machines...

objects.title: THE BACKSTREET
objects.text: They clearly weren't from here. The way they moved around was too relaxed. Not a hint of fear on their face, despite the district they were in. They ignored the prostitutes who tried to approach them and the scrawny junkies begging for money. Calmly, they walked into the alley...

objects.title: THE JUNGLE
objects.text: The deep jungles of your homeworld are filled with deadly dangers. Yet it's not unusual for intrepid treasure seekers to venture into the marsh in search of riches buried in ruined temples lost in the forest. The one you met that day, however, had come for a completely different reason...

objects.title: THE BALLROOM
objects.text: It was a beautiful place where the aristocrats of your homeworld met regularly. A gigantic bay window giving a bird's eye view of the city. Sweet music making the air vibrate. Women dressed in ravishing dresses and exotic jewelry. And... this strange outsider.

objects.title: THE VILLAGE
objects.text: You never knew where the attack came from, nor the identity of those who that night burned the houses of your village and massacred its inhabitants. Bandits? Mercenaries ? Luckily, they didn't pay any attention to you and left quickly after their crime.

objects.title: The Slave Market
objects.text: Half-naked, a collar around your neck, you were dragged like a dog onto the stage to be presented to potential buyers. In the midst of the yelling and bidding, they calmly raised their hand and stated their price. There was an instant silence. Ten minutes later, you belonged to them. They then removed your chains.

objects.title: The Little Beggar
objects.text: They stopped in front of you, young beggar in rags with emaciated cheeks. Accustomed to the regular beatings by the members of the Night Patrol, you cowered, prepared to get beaten up, but they simply put one hand on your shoulder and said, "Stand up and follow me."

objects.title: The Hunted
objects.text: You were running away from something terrible that day. Probably a ferocious beast. Abandoned by the members of your tribe for a crime that the clan chief had accused you of, you would have died if you hadn't bumped into them, in the middle of a clearing, radiating an aura infinitely more dangerous than any local predator.

objects.title: The Humble One
objects.text: You were just a discreet servant in charge of bringing drinks to the guests and making yourself as noiseless as possible. Yet the outsider, as soon as they entered, had laid their eyes on you and never stopped staring at you. It was only after several hours of observation that they approached you and made you an offer.

objects.title: The Orphan
objects.text: They found you the next day among the fuming ruins of your home. Slowly, they forced you to let go of your mother's corpse, which you had clung to all night without realizing it. They grabbed you by the arm and took you away from the mutilated bodies that had once been those of your parents and friends.

objects.title: The Pickpocket
objects.text: They seemed harmless and their purse was full. The opportunity was too tempting, and your belly too empty. Hidding in the crowd, you approached silently and... their hand grabbed your wrist, lighteningfast. You thought your last hour had come but they just smiled. "Not bad," they said. "But you're lacking practice. I could make you faster."

objects.title: The Ambush
objects.text: Gangs of street urchins are not uncommon in such places. The territory of yours included the alleyway they had just walked down. The knife you aimed at their throat didn't even touch them. They struck five times with their bare hands, and all four members of your gang collapsed, dead. You didn't. When they walked out of the alley, you followed them. You had passed the test.

objects.title: The Hunter
objects.text: Within your tribe, tradition dictates that one must kill to be considered a true warrior. The one you chose that day for your initiation rite did not seem particularly dangerous. A lost traveler, perhaps... You realised too late that in this story, you were the prey. To this day, you still don't know why they didn't kill you on the spot. You never saw your tribe again.

objects.title: The Noble
objects.text: As the heir of one of the most influential men on the planet, most people trembled and sweated when they spoke to you. Not this one. You had never seen them before in your life and yet they approached you as if they were an old friend. Smiling, they bent down to whisper something in your ear that you'd never forget.

objects.title: The Amnesiac
objects.text: What happened that night was probably too horrible for your brain to process. Your mind broke and left you amnesic, wandering between the ruined houses without remembering your name or your past. When you try to remember the face of your parents, only the face of that Master comes to mind, the one who found you and took you with them.

rows.title: SOMETHING CAUGIHT THEIR EYE
rows.titleText:
The potential they spotted in you would probably not have been enough to make them choose you as their disciple if they had not felt something deeper within you, a special resonance with the Dark Side of the Force. 

Pick a Drive

objects.title: AMBITION
objects.text: Whether a rampant obsession to become the strongest has been hanging deep inside of you for a long time, or whether you are consumed with the idea of ruling and holding in the palm of your hand the destinies of billions of living beings, what you desire is to reach the top. Crushing all those who stand in your way does not frighten you in the least. Be wary, though: that kind of hunger can hardly be satiated and you'll always want more.

objects.title: DESPAIR
objects.text: It seems like something inside you broke a long time ago. Hope. Joy. A particular event in your life, or the environment in which you lived, has plunged you into a bottomless pit of despair. As they say, fear leads to anger. Anger leads to hate. Hate leads to suffering. And nothing in the world leads more quickly to the Dark side of the Force than suffering. It only took a second for the one who found you to read all this in your eyes, and much more.

objects.title: HEDONISM
objects.text: The galaxy is vast and has no shortage of virtuous men... nor does it lack degenerates of all kinds. You are a condensate of all sorts of perversions and unhealthy desires that the Light side of the Force cannot fulfill in any way. Satisfying the forbidden desires that haunt your thoughts can only be done to the detriment of any bond, any friendship, any love. The way of the hedonist is the way of solitude... and selfishness. And who knows more about selfishness than a Sith?

objects.title: VENGEANCE
objects.text: Unlike some - so consumed by their immense anger that they blindly unleash it around them - yours has a very specific target. Someone or something has wronged you and the only thing that still urges you to live is the idea of revenge: Revenge against a particular person, an organization, or society in general. Your Master promised you that they could help you in this vengeance by making you stronger. For that, you are ready to follow them to Hell.

objects.title: EVIL
objects.text: Evil. In its purest form. There's no better way to turn it. What you have in you is not mere pettiness or a kind of cynicism that makes you indifferent to cruelty. It's a thirst for blood. A willingness to inflict suffering out of sheer pleasure. A deep sadism that you have, until now, never been able to indulge or fully explore, forced to hide it in order to survive. The one who found you, however, offered you the opportunity to fully immerse yourself in it.

rows.title: RELATIONSHIP
rows.titleText:
Every Sith Master is led to form a special and unique type of relationship with their Disciple. Yours was no exception. 

Pick a form of teacher-student relationship:

objects.title: TYRANNICAL
objects.text: Like many Sith apprentices, the relationship you had with your Master was based on fear. They took great care, from the very start of your training, to make it clear that they could kill you in the blink of an eye or inflict immense pain at will. They taught you to hate them, and thus prepared you, without you being aware of it yet, for your final Test.

objects.title: ABUSIVE
objects.text: Your Master made you their pawn, entirely devoted to them and their plans. They manipulated your emotions and exploited a sentimental or psychological lever to constantly accentuate their ascendancy on you, knowing your weaknesses and flaws better than anyone else and using them to shape you according to their desires.

objects.title: FORMAL
objects.text: They were the Master and you the Disciple. Nothing more, nothing less. If they was ever cordial to you, they always remained extremely cold, considering you without emotion or attachment, some times even without the slightest interest. They erected a wall of ice between you from the very start of your training. To protect themself from you, perhaps?

objects.title: ELUSIVE
objects.text: As surprising as it may seem, you were almost never in direct contact with your Master. Oh, throughout your training you felt their invisible hand weighing on you and manipulating you from afar, like a puppeteer, recognizing their touch on every obstacle in your way, but they took great care to show themself as little as possible, remaining in the shadows and shaping you through their twisted plans and confusing schemes.

objects.title: ECCENTRIC
objects.text: Your Master was quite the thing, verging on madness. You were never comfortable with them, and maybe that was their intention. One day they could talk to you with affection, like a parent to their child, and the next day they could punish you terribly for daring to look them in the eyes. You were always on your guard, ready for anything.

rows.title: PHILOSOPHY
rows.titleText:
The Jedis are far from being a homogeneous organization in terms of morals and ideas, and the Sith are even more divergent than they are. Each Sith Lord has their own worldview, their own aspirations and their own distinct methodology when it comes to training a Disciple. 

Pick up to three Ideologies to which your Master adheres.

objects.title: WARRIOR'S HONOR
objects.text: Your Master has taught you that a fight without honor is repugnant, and that a victory is only worthwhile if it is achieved in an honorable manner, without chea ting or trickery. They whose skills and strength are not enough to defeat their opponent is not a real Sith.

objects.title: THE END JUSTIFIES...
objects.text: Your Master believed that a true Sith should go to any length to achieve their goal, no matter the moral implications of their actions, whether it is murdering colleagues or backstabbing a foe. They taught you countless dirty tricks to use in a fight.

objects.title: CREDO FIRST
objects.text: Your Master was a passionate adherent to the Credo of the Sith, believing that the current structure of the organization is the only one possible and that questioning the Sith Code is unacceptable. For them, any divergence was cause for execution.

objects.title: UNORTHODOX DOCTRINE
objects.text: Your Master cultivated a particularly divergent opinion from the norm among the Sith. Perhaps they were questioning the Rule of Two or aspiring to a profound reform of Sith philosophy. Perhaps their divergence was related to their approach to the Force. Perhaps they were even slowly leaning towards the Light Side...

objects.title: CAREFUL PLANNER
objects.text: Your Master's policy was never to act without first knowing their opponent in details. They instructed you in the art of developing multiple contingency plans to anticipate any possible situation, and made you an excellent analyst and tactician.

objects.title: ADAPTABILITY IS KEY
objects.text: Your Master was convinced of the superiority of instinct and adaptability over planning. Flexibility should always prevail on rigid plans. During your training, they constantly tested your intuition and developed your sense of improvisation, whether in combat or on a more global scale.

objects.title: MY SUCCESSOR...
objects.text: Whether you were aware of it or not, your Master saw in you their successor. Thus, they centered your training on an academic transmission of their own techniques, passing on to you their style and their knowledge to make their skills live on through you, after their death.

objects.title: YOU'RE NOT ME
objects.text: Your Master wanted you to develop your own style rather than imitate theirs. As such, they trained you only in the basics, then engaged you in frequent, and brutal sparring matches, encouraging you to improvise and develop your own combat techniques to counter them.

objects.title: SITH SCHOLAR
objects.text: "Power through knowledge." your Master always said. They were a scholar versed in many sciences and had long traveled across the galaxy to study the history of the Sith or to accumulate knowledge about peoples and cultures. They shared a lot of it with you.

objects.title: AUSTERITY
objects.text: Comfort and daily pleasures were banished with your Master. During your training, they imposed a spartan lifestyle and constant deprivation, strengthening your self-discipline, tolerance of hunger, thirst and pain, and taught you many techniques for surviving in hostile territory.

objects.title: LAVISH LIFESTYLE
objects.text: The finer things in life such as banquets and well-tailored suits were greatly appreciated by your Master. You were initiated into all the mundane pleasures they indulged in on a regular basis. Let's hope it didn't soften you up too much.

objects.title: TROPHY HUNTER
objects.text: Your Master had a habit of collecting something special on the opponents they had defeated. Perhaps the sabers of the Jedi that they had killed, or perhaps more macabre elements, such as the eyes of their enemies... Either way, they often carried their trophies with them.

objects.title: THIRST FOR FREEDOM
objects.text: Your Master considered the dark side of the Force as a means to emancipate ones self from the established rules and shackles of society. For them, what characterizes a Sith, more than their strength, is their freedom. They cultivated in you a taste for travel and an aversion to authority.

objects.title: WAY OF STABILITY
objects.text: According to your Master, peace and happiness within the galaxy can only be achieved through political stability and a strong regime. For them, the Dark Side of the Force was above all a means of obtaining political power and ruling over the masses with absolute authority.

objects.title: PERSONAL RITES
objects.text: Your Master regularly performed a short ritual of their own. Perhaps a strange form of meditation before a fight, or they tattooed symbols on their body... Either way, it was of great importance to them. Did you adopt this ritual?

objects.title: STRANGE INTEREST
objects.text: Some Sith are not only interested in fighting and power-seeking but can develop passions for unusual topics. Your Master was one of those and taught you many things about a particular field in which they were an expert: Cooking perhaps, or music, medicine, oenology?

objects.title: DARING IN ALL THINGS
objects.text: Your Master was known within the Sith Order as someone who was particularly daring, constantly seeking to put themself in danger, challenging authority, popular beliefs and often common sense. You've adopted a part of their character.

objects.title: RACISM
objects.text: Whatever species your Master belonged to, they regarded it as naturally superior to the other races of the galaxy and greatly despised those they called the "sub-beings". They owned and mistreated many "inferior" slaves and servants.

objects.title: NEVER STOP LEARNING
objects.text: Your Master was surprisingly humble for a Sith Lord, considering that the apprenticeship of the Force and the Lightsaber is an endless journey, and that there is always someone better than you in the galaxy. This principle has shaped you throughout your training, and still does today.

objects.title: WANT TO EAT?
objects.text: Your Master taught you in a particularly harsh way that what you wanted you had to earn. Want to eat? Go hunt by yourself. Want something? Buy it yourself or steal it. With them, you were not owed anything, not comfort, not equipment, not even medical care.

objects.title: ETIQUETTE
objects.text: Whether because of noble origins or simply because of their admiration for civilization, your Master was a very refined Sith who loved to frequent the upper galactic society. They taught you rhetoric, good manners, and all sorts of things useful in the aristocracy.

objects.title: THE BEAST IN YOU
objects.text: Your Master regarded civilization as a perversion created by soft, weak men. For them, true nobility was represented by the primitive savages populating the feral worlds. They taught you many of their hunting techniques, as well as some of their combat skills.

objects.title: CLEAN HANDS
objects.text: Why do something that others can do for you? Following this principle, your Master had developed a vast network of agents and spies throughout the galaxy, and surrounded themself with several units of soldiers, allowing them to delegate the majority of their tasks to their agents and supervise them from afar.

objects.title: HERO OF HIS OWN STORY
objects.text: Surprisingly, your Master never considered themself a "bad guy". On the contrary, for them, the violence they used was always a means of doing Good, even indirectly. Whether killing, stealing, destroying or torturing, they saw all their actions as a necessary evil that had to be done.

rows.title: HEADQUARTERS
rows.titleText:
Every true Sith Lord has a base that they use as a launching point for their operations and as a sanctuary in the case of a forced retreat. And yours? Where did they take you after they found you?

Pick one Headquarters.

objects.title: MOTHERSHIP
objects.text: Your Master owned a huge ship that they used as a mobile base with which they traveled from planet to planet. The enormous crew that ran the ship was entirely at their service and included mechanics, soldiers, droids, etc...

objects.title: CITADEL
objects.text: Your Master's headquarters was a vast military fortress occupied by a massive garrison of soldiers. The place included many combat training facilities and the latest military technology available in the galaxy.

objects.title: PALACE
objects.text: Your Master had set up their base on a small paradise-like planet. The place looked like a vast, incredibly luxurious villa, maintained by hordes of slaves and Droids ready to fulfill all their master's desires.

objects.title: OLD TEMPLE
objects.text: Your Master had chosen as their base an ancient Sith temple, forgotten by all, lost deep in the misty lands of a planet that has never been charted. Its location was untraceable. The place, majestic but sinister, was imbued with the dark side of the Force

objects.title: NO HOME
objects.text: Your Master had no headquarters strictly speaking, perhaps out of personal conviction or lack of means. Or perhaps they did have a secret base but have never revealed its location to you. Either way, you have never seen it.

rows.title: TRAINING FOCUS
rows.titleText: Every Sith dreams of being perfect in everything, but few achieve it, except for a few geniuses. Very early on, your Master identified your strengths and weaknesses and guided your training to maximize your potential.

objects.title: DUELIST
objects.text: It only took a few sparrings for your Master to understand that they were dealing with a virtuoso swordsman, a born duellist. It was only necessary for them to demonstrate a technique to you once so that you could understand it and be able to reproduce it perfectly. Leaving aside your study of the Force, they focused almost exclusively on your training in close combat.

objects.title: LIGHTSABER ORIENTED
objects.text: You've always been better with a Lightsaber than with the Force, and your Master soon noticed this. Rather than waste time making you study the advanced mysteries of the Force in depth, they preferred to make you spend more time practicing your katas with a blade and exercising your reflexes and natural dexterity,

objects.title: BALANCED STUDENT
objects.text: Since you showed equivalent dispositions in terms of Force proficiency and Lightsaber skill, your Master decided to divide your time equally between these two disciplines, leaving no part untouched to make you a well-rounded Sith with extensive knowledge of the Force and a very high level of combat expertise.

objects.title: FORCE ORIENTED
objects.text: From the very start of your training, your Master noticed that you had certain ease in manipulating the Force and in understanding some particularly obscure concepts. As a result, they decided to train you to develop your Force powers rather than your lightsaber skills.

objects.title: WIZARD
objects.text: You are one of those rare individuals endowed with an exceptional affinity with the Force, an almost natural grasp of its principles. Very quickly, your Master sensed in you a very deep resonance with the Force, which flows through you with incredible fluidity. Decided not to waste your potential, they immersed you in a training dedicated almost exclusively to developing your Force abilities.

objects.title: STANDARD
objects.text: The most common type of Lightsaber is the standard Lightsaber, adapted to all existing fighting styles, extremely versatile, can be used with one or two hands, and comes in several different lengths depending on the size of the fighter. The vast majority of Sith use a standard saber.

objects.title: DUAL WIELDING
objects.text: Much more uncommon, the simultaneous wielding of two blades requires either natural ambidextrousness on the part of the combatant, or extremely difficult training to maximize coordination and synergy between the two hands. However, dual wielding offers unique possibilities in close combat.

objects.title: DOUBLE BLADE
objects.text: Quite rare among the Jedi, more common among the Sith but still unusual, the double lightsaber is the most difficult weapon to handle, and the most dangerous for its practitioner. However, experts in the art of fighting with this type of saber are incredibly more lethal than others and excel in aggressive and fast moves.

objects.title: EMPTY HANDS
objects.text:
In order to attune even more with the Force, you have made the radical decision to do without the Lightsaber altogether, focusing entirely, in combat, on your Force abilities and nothing else, whether attacking or defending.

By picking this option, you convert your Style Point into two additional Force Points.

rows.title: FIGHTING STYLE
rows.titleText: Although every Sith, as they gain experience and survive battles, gradually develop a fighting style of their own, with techniques that only they know and really master, it is still possible to divide the main fighting styles of the Sith into six distinct categories, each with its advantages and disadvantages for their practitioners. What style did your Master put the emphasis on during your training? Pick at least one Style, unless you have chosen the Empty Hands option. Unlocking a Style costs 1 Style Point. Unlocking an Advanced Skill costs 1 Blade Point. You can't buy Advanced Skills belonging to Styles that you didn't unlock. Unlocking multiple Styles leads you to develop a unique style, mixing techniques from several disciplines.

objects.text: Duelists, Lightsaber Oriented and Balanced fighters can convert 2 Blade Points into 1 Style Point. They can do this only once.

objects.title: STRONG STYLE
objects.text: The philosophy on which the Strong Style is based is to strike few but hard, to favor heavy and few blows, all individually capable of overpowering the opponent, over combinations of weak strikes. It's a direct and pragmatic style that requires its practitioners to combine their body weight and muscular strength with the energizing drug of anger so that the execution of their attacks will land with enough force to crack armors or disarm opponents. To master this style, you had to undergo extremely intense muscular exercises throughout your training.

objects.title: HEAVY PARRIES
objects.text: Your Master has taught you how to apply your physical strength not only in your attacks but also in your parries. When using this style to defend yourself, you can deflect a blade with enough force to make your foe lose their balance throw them to the ground or break their guard. This requires a certain talent for analysis and a keen sense of timing.

objects.title: THE FIERY DANCE
objects.text: The technique known as "The Fiery Dance" consists in sequence of three consecutive swings delivered from three different angles, with Increasing power, the third strike being twice as strong as the previous one and considered almost unstoppable. Strong Style practitioners are very fond of this combination that can be repeated several times during a fight by modifying the striking angles.

objects.title: MODULAR STRENGTH
objects.text: Through meditation exercises, more than physical reinforcement, you have learned to modulate your physical strength with precision, either to reduce it significantly in the middle of a series of blows thus throwing your opponent off balance or to exceed your limits for a short time at the cost of exhaustion. In the latter case, you can almost double your maximum strength briefly.

objects.title: D'JAAR SAI
objects.text: The "D'jaar Sai" strike is a dangerous technique consisting in switching from two-handed to one-handed grip on your saber in the middle of a movement, executing a one-armed parry and, simultaneously, hardening your free fist with the Force and violently hitting your opponent in the throat. Variations of this skill may involve punching your opponent in the chest or face.

objects.title: ELEGANT STYLE
objects.text: This style is almost the antithesis of the previous one. Based on a perverted form of the Makashi, the Elegant Style seems similar to antique fencing. The practitioner is encouraged to stand in profile and hold his weapon in one hand. Its techniques rely on precision and efficiency through fluid strikes and lightning-fast thrusts, targeting the opponent's weak spots. Masters of the Elegant Style do not parry the blows, they deflect them gracefully from the tip of their blade and counter-attack swiftly. They also use their balance and footwork to outmaneuver their foe in a duel, while remaining extremely stable themselves.

objects.title: IAIDO
objects.text: You've been trained in the rare and spectacular art of activating your Lightsaber and striking in a single, fluid and continuous, lightning fast movement, in order to end the fight in a flash, before the opponent can make the slightest move. Experts in this technique can turn their Lightsaber off and on repeatedly in rapid succession, in a duel, to make their attacks completely unpredictable.

objects.title: GO WITH THE FLOW
objects.text: Following the principles of various martial arts dedicated to unarmed combat, and transposing them to fencing, Sith have developed party techniques that allow them to deflect gracefully their opponent's strikes with the tip of their blade and turn the momentum of their attacks against them in order to unbalance them or suddenly bypass their defenses and execute a lethal counterattack.

objects.title: FEINT MASTER
objects.text: Your Master has taught you whole range of complex known by very few fighters, making you a very difficult opponent to fight. When they think you're swinging from above, you swing from below. When your strike comes from the left, it actually hits from the right. You control the trajectory of your blade with surgical precision and know how to use it with subtlety and intelligence.

objects.title: DISARMING STRIKE
objects.text: Few Sith direct their fighting style towards disarming preferring to strike to kill, but you have chosen to dedicate a large part of your training to the art of disarming your foe, whether by cutting off their hand or slicing the hilt of their sword with your blade. This gives you a distinct advantage in combat, as very few Lightsaber fighters, whether Jedi or Sith, are trained to deal with this unorthodox style.

objects.title: DEFENSIVE STYLE
objects.text: Rare are the Sith who adopt this style of fighting, somewhat similar to the Soresu, but it is sometimes taught as a secondary style, in addition to another. The Defensive Style, as its name suggests, revolves around successive parries and economy of movement and effort. Its practitioners adopt a relatively static posture, centred on defence and sometimes quick dodges through imperceptible bust and hip movements. The fundamental purpose of this style is to exhaust the opponent and watch for the slightest opening in his guard, offering the opportunity to counterattack. It requires a keen sense of observation and extraordinary reflexes.

objects.title: REPEL SHOTS
objects.text: Like Jedi who have undergone extensive Shien training, you have become an expert in the art of not only intercepting blaster fires with your Lightsaber, but more importantly, of sending them back in any direction, including that of the shooter. You have also developed the ability to deflect shots with your eyes dosed and in any position, through hours of intense and risky training.

objects.title: ALZAAR KYN
objects.text: The "Alzaar Kyn" is a derivative from the Defensive Style allowing its users to predict their opponent's attacks, before they even launch them through the on the footwork and subtle to know where their attacks will come from, only their feet and you're able to react to the most unpredictable strikes.

objects.title: 360° DEFENSE
objects.text: By infusing greater mobility into your Defensive Style, as well as swirling and spinning parry techniques, you have become able to block attacks not only from a single opponent, but also from a group of opponents attacking you simultaneously from multiple sides, and even from behind. Your Master described your style as similar to "a protective sphere without a single weakness".

objects.title: VICIOUS BAIT
objects.text: Particularly audacious, this technique allows you to bait your opponent and lure him to open his guard by exposing a false weak point in your defenses that he will be tempted to attack. Of course, this is just a trick that allows you to create a counter-attack opportunity yourself rather than waiting for one. You've slayed many foes with this skill.

objects.title: ACROBATIC STYLE
objects.text: Fundamentally opposed to the previous style, the Acrobatic Style is totally oriented towards attack and aggressiveness, based on Force-assisted somersaults and leaping strikes. A practitioner of this style is in constant motion, delivering countless blows to his opponent from many directions, including from the airs, at high speed. Its masters appear like a blur to their foes, spinning, striking, spinning again, dodging rather than parrying, evading incoming strikes with spectacular backflips and acrobatics... Needless to say that this style is very risky due to the fact that it neglects defense and exhausts the stamina of its users quickly.

objects.title: FLYING KICK
objects.text: To add variety and unpredictability to your moves, you've learned to combine your jumps and somersaults with flying kicks, which you are able to perform in mid-air after or before a Lightsaber strike. You have also become able to reinforce your lees with the Force to give even more power to your kicks, which are now capable of breaking bones or knocking your opponent out.

objects.title: THE WIND STEPS
objects.text: Having realized that the outcome of a fight depends on a multitude of factors, including the location of the duel, you have earned how to make the most of your environment in combat. You are able to run on walls, jump over your opponent by Ieaning against an obstacle, use every innocuous element of your surrounding as a stepping stone to launch an attack, to jump from wall to wall...

objects.title: MESMERIZING DANCE
objects.text: Using ancient Sith battle manuals, you've developed a very strange and elusive fighting style, similar to a kind of dance. Your movements are hypnotic and tend to confuse your opponents, who sometimes feel like they're facing several enemies at once instead of one, or try to parry blows that don't exist. Facing you is like fighting an intangible mirage.

objects.title: ANTELOPE STRIKE
objects.text: This very challenging and visually spectacular technique consists in amplifying your speed of movement for a fraction of a second by using the Force going well beyond your muscular limits, and, thanks to a series of complex and very fast steps, moving behind your opponent's back, in a flash, to deliver a deadly strike. Eh.. Nothing personal kiddo.

objects.title: FORCE-BASED STYLE
objects.text: "Victory through the Force." Only for Wizards, Force Oriented and Balanced fighters. This style is the one that the Sith most often turn to when they have a special affinity with the Force. Although rather standard in terms of pure fencing techniques, it is characterized by the inclusion of Force-based attacks in combat, such as telekinetic pulls and shoves used in sync with lightsaber strikes. It gives its practitioners great versatility and the ability to engage in combat from a distance, for example by telekinesically throwing objects of the environement at their opponents, before following up with light saber strikes.

objects.title: FLOATING BLADES
objects.text: Very few Sith have the talent to manipulate their Lightsabers remotely, by telekinesis, with enough intensity and precision to make them lethal. Some of the most gifted are even able to control several sabers at once and swirl them around to attack or protect themselves. However, this kind of technique is extremely psychologically exhausting and can only be used in special circumstances, when the Sith has time to focus.

objects.title: LIGHTNING BLOCK
objects.text: Over time, as Force Lightning became one of the favorite abilities of the Sith talented with the Force, it became vital for the Jedi to learn how to protect themselves from it, as well as for the Sith themselves. This skill allows you to parry Force Lightning bolts with the blade of your Lightsaber and even, with some efforts, send them straight back to your opponent. Perhaps with even more power.

objects.title: SHOCKWAVE
objects.text: Through combat meditation exercises, you've learned how to make the Force flow along your Lightsaber. Thanks to this, you are now able to i accompany each of your swings with a Force shock wave that acts as a Force Push applied in the direction of your strike. This way, you don't need to free one of your hands to repulse your opponent with the Force, just attack him with your sword.

objects.title: FORCE PARRY
objects.text: You've learned to parry not with your sword, but directly intercept your opponent's Lightsaber with the Force before it hits you, and stop it in mid-air. You can also slightly deviate the trajectory of your opponent's strikes in combat without them noticing, giving the impression that you are an absolute master of dodging. Of course, it's all very exhausting.

objects.title: FURIOUS STYLE
objects.text: This style is probably the one that best incarnates the dark side of the Force since it requires its practitioners to let themselves be completely submerged by violent emotions in combat, especially anger. It is the most vicious form of lightsaber combat, filled with both fury and malignant grace. The opponent is flooded with a barrage of chaotic and erratic blows, delivered with a combination of speed and bestial force, halfway between the heavy blows of the Strong Style and the fast and aerial attacks of the Acrobatic Style. The challenge for a practitioner of this style is to maintain his lucidity despite the rage that grows as the fight goes on.

objects.title: TAUNTING CRY
objects.text: In combat, you've made provocation your specialty, not hesitating to taunt your opponent to make fatal mistakes. However, your emotions are so powerful that your screams are infused with the dark side of the Force and your fury is communicative, capable of blinding a previously serene opponent with sudden rage and madness that they, unlike you, are not prepared to face.

objects.title: TERROR
objects.text: In combat, you are absolutely terrifying. It is not only the screams you utter or your grunts, or the senseless rage in your blows, but even your appearance changes Lightning flashes dance in your eyes, veins appear on your face, the dark side of the Force exudes from you. Facing you without panicking and dropping your Lightsaber requires a courage and self-control that very few warriors possess, even among the Jedi.

objects.title: COLD BLOOD
objects.text: In contrast to many practitioners of the Furious Style, you have committed yourself to full days of meditation during your training to strengthen your mind. This allows you to keep your lucidity in combat, while exploiting your anger in an optimal way. Your emotions do not control - you, you control them, and your movements are closer to those of the Jedi Vaapad than the Sith Juyo.

objects.title: HULAR ZEKEM
objects.text: The "Hular Zekem" is a derivative of the Furious Style, even more chaotic and unpredictable than the original. You yourself are almost incapable of knowing where your sword will strike. Its trajectories and angles of attack seem completely incoherent and without continuity, as if it had become sentient and crazy.

rows.title: FORCE POWERS
rows.titleText:
It is essential for a Sith to master the Force in order to survive. However, the relationship a Sith develops with the Force is unique to each. Is the Force a weapon you use to crush your enemies? A tool dedicated to the fulfillment of your ambitions? An obscure concept that you fear? A omnipresent entity that you are trying to explore and understand? 

Buy Force Powers with your Force Points.

objects.text: You get the basic Force powers that every Sith must master for free: Force Push (telekinetic repulsion of objects), Force Pull (telekinetic attraction of objects), Force Jump (telekinetic amplification of jump height), and a few minor powers that act on you passively and make you more sensitive, faster, and stronger than an ordinary being.

objects.title: LEVEL 1 ABILITIES
objects.text: Each one costs 1 Force Point.

objects.title: FORCE LIGHTNING
objects.text: Emblematic Sith Force ability, consisting in delivering powerful electrical discharges to a target through the user's fingers and hands. The intensity varies according to many factors, such as the user's talent.

objects.title: FORCE BARRIER
objects.text: Defensive technique composed of Force energy, used to block out any potentially deadly elements such as environmental hazards or any type of projectiles like blaster fires. Takes the form of a wall or a sphere.

objects.title: FORCE SENSE
objects.text: Telepathic extension of the user's mind, allowing to feel the living beings around you -even through the walls- or any movement in a certain radius. Also considerably heightens the five senses.

objects.title: BATTLE PRECOGNITION
objects.text: Allows one to sense and foretell the flows of the Force while engaged in battle. Used to predict an opponent's intentions or the trajectory of blaster shots before they are fired. Also amplifies reflexes.

objects.title: FORCE PAIN
objects.text: Telepathic projectile that produces unbearable pain waves in the brain of a target. Can cause nausea and dizziness. Used for torture. Requires high concentration and thus, is difficult to use in combat.

objects.title: ADVANCED FORCE PUSH
objects.text: Force Push applied with sufficient intensity to lift several men off the ground and throw them over a distance of at least 10 metres, or break down a metal door whose reinforcement is not too strong.

objects.title: FORCE SPEED
objects.text: Running speed amplification for a split second. Allows the user to dash in a straight line of 4-5 meters max, so fast that they appear as a blur to any observer. Can be used successively to cover longer distances.

objects.title: FORCE CHOKE
objects.text: Telekinetic use of Force, oftentimes with a grip-like gesture, to choke or strangle a victim. Restricts blood circulation and airflow. Can be used to lift a victim off the ground, holding them by the neck.

objects.title: CONSUME ESSENCE
objects.text: Allows a dark side Force-user to feed on the fear, hatred, physical pain, or other negative emotions of others-in a certain radius- to make himself more powerful or recover energy in combat.

objects.title: ADVANCED LIGHTNING
objects.text: Powerful electric discharge branching out into dozens of smaller forks, thus allowing the dark side Force user to reach multiple targets simultaneously, without any loss of intensity.

objects.title: FORCE STUN
objects.text: Allows the user to induce a target into catatonic state. With enough practice, the effects can extend to several targets at once. Beings creatures with a high degree of willpower can resist the effects of this ability, as well as droids.

objects.title: FORCE HORROR
objects.text: Creation of frightening visual and sound illusions in the mind of the target, intended to scare them away, or intimidate them, divert their attention, or break their concentration during a fight.

objects.title: FORCE RAGE
objects.text: Channeling of all negative emotions into the heart of the user - such as fear, despair, pain, anger - to convert them into a sudden and intense burst of rage, boosting every physical ability for a few minutes.

objects.title: FORCE SLOW
objects.text: Ability that clouds the target's mind, causing them to slow down both mentally and physically during combat, as if they were completely exhausted. At higher degrees of intenity, can even debilitate the victim permanently.

objects.title: FORCE CLOAK
objects.text: Sending of a telepathic command that propagates concentrically around the user, like a ripple, and persuades the surrounding minds that the user is insignificant or even non-existent.

objects.title: FORCE FLASH
objects.text: Allows the user to disable holocams and surrounding electrical devices through a flash of unnatural energy. Also able to blind an opponent in close-combat and neutralize the primary functions of droids for a short time.

objects.title: FORCE WAVE
objects.text: Same as Advanced Force Push but applied as a multidirectional shockwave that violently impacts any object or person around the user in a radius of 3 to 5 meters.

objects.title: MEMORY WALK
objects.text: Consists of reaching into the victim's mind, forcing them to relive all the worst memories of their life, both painful ones and ones that were merely embarrassing, over and over again, for a few minutes that seem like hours.

objects.title: SHADOW VISION
objects.text: Focus of the Force in the eyes of the user. Allows you to see in the dark, zoom in as if you were looking through binoculars, or, with a lot of practice, see through walls. Causes headaches if used too long.

objects.title: LEVEL 2 ABILITIES
objects.text:
Only available for Wizards, Force Oriented and Balanced fighters.
Each one costs 2 Force Points.

objects.title: FORCE CORRUPT
objects.text: Mind control through hypnosis. Dark-side ability that can temporarily manipulate the minds of other sentient beings and make them serve one's own cause. Can be resisted through high degree of willpower.

objects.title: FORCE CRUSH
objects.text: Violent ability consisting in lifting a target-droid, person, even vehicle-into the air with the Force and, as they are floating, making their body implode by applying enormous pressure on it.

objects.title: FORCE TEMPEST
objects.text: Powerful ability, allowing the user to project Force Lightning from all of their limbs simultaneously in an impressive whirlwind that encircles their body, inflicting damage to everyone around them.

objects.title: INVISIBILITY
objects.text: Telekinetic bending of light particles and sound waves to render a practitioner virtually invisible to the naked eye. Requires a quasi-surgical mastery of the Force and a high degree of concentration. Cannot be used in combat.

objects.title: MASS CONFUSION
objects.text: Same as Force Horror but applied to anyone within a certain radius of the user. The illusions are even more vivid and difficult to resist due to collective hysteria.

objects.title: FORCE EXPLOSION
objects.text: Same as Force Wave but at least five times more powerful, capable of pulverizing minor buildings and dismembering surrounding people, even those wearing armor.

objects.title: FORCE DRAIN
objects.text: Dark-Side counterpart of Jedi Force Healing. Heals the user's wounds - through cell regeneration - by absorbing the vital energy of a victim, causing them to age at an accelerated rate as you apply your power to them.

objects.title: FORCE SCREAM
objects.text: Force exertion that manifests through a scream of rage or grief and echoes through time and space, disrupting the flow of the Force in an extremely large radius, physically and mentally hurting every Force user able to feel it.

objects.title: FORCE STASIS
objects.text: Ability to telekinetically freeze an object in mid-air or paralyze someone completely. The higher the velocity of the target before the power is applied, the more difficult it is to keep it static for a long time.

objects.title: HEAVY TELEKINESIS
objects.text: Ability to telekinetically lift, throw, and manipulate massive objects such as large groups of people, space ships, large trees or heavy boulders.

objects.title: FORCE CITADEL
objects.text: Same as Force Barrier but far more powerful and electrified, hurting anyone who touches it. Can protect its user from explosions, lightsaber strikes or forces able to pulverize entire buildings.

objects.title: FORCE COMPASS
objects.text: Allows its user to feel and recognize the Force signature of any Force user that has been in the area, and to follow their trail without losing it, even from planet to planet. Also useful for detection Force user at great distances.

objects.title: FORCE DESTRUCTION
objects.text: Creation of a massive and extremely dense field that can be thrown in any direction. Can be used against large areas, vaporizing anyone and anything who is exposed to it, even structure like walls and reinforced doors.

objects.title: INSENSIBILITY
objects.text: Half Force manipulation, half self-hypnosis, this ability allows the user to completely shut himself off from his physical sensations and thus nullify pain or any feeling of exhaustion.

objects.title: LEVEL 3 ABILITIES
objects.text:
Only available for Wizards. 
Each one costs 3 Force Points

objects.title: DEADLY SIGHT
objects.text: Projection of ultraintense hatred through a sinister glare onto the target -as long as the target is into the practitioner's range of vision. Skin is dissolved instantly. Extremities are vaporized. The victim's flesh burns and smokes in a few secondes, causing an unbearable agony.

objects.title: LIFE RITUAL
objects.text:
Requires two Level 2 Abilities 
Ritual of tremendous power designed to absorb the vital energy of a very large number of people, as well as plants and minerals, in order to prolong one's own life expectancy and achieve a form of pseudoimmortality. Can cause the death of a planet.

objects.title: LIGHTNING CATACLYSM
objects.text: An incredibly intense electrical discharge that spreads over tens of meters and can reach more than a hundred people. Causes sufficient heat to liquefy the metal and disintegrate the flesh in a split of second.

objects.title: MIDI-CHLORIAN MANIPULATION
objects.text: Manipulation of midichlorians on a cellular level. Ability to perform amazing miracles or unnatural abominations (depending on your point of view), such as creating life from the Force, producing biological mutations, etc...

objects.title: FORCE MAELSTROM
objects.text: Same as Force Explosion but of such power that the shock wave devastates everything in a radius wide enough to pulverize several large surrounding buildings, with enough intensity to throw heavy vehicles tens of meters into the air.

objects.title: SURGICAL TELEKINESIS
objects.text: Telekinesis applied with great precision, to the point of being able to kill a living being with a thought by rupturing a vein or crushing neurons in the brain. Also allows to render a limb inoperative by telekinetically cutting a nerve or tendon.

objects.title: SEVER FORCE
objects.text: A rare ability that allows you to interrupt a living being's connection with the Force, depriving them momentarily (or over a long period of time) of any use of the Force. When applied to yourself, makes you undetectable to Force Sense or Force Compass.

objects.title: FORCE PORTAL
objects.text: Manipulation of the fabric of space itself through the Force. Creation of space portals allowing the user to move instantaneously over immense distances, for example from one planet to another. Consumes enormous amounts of energy.

objects.title: TIME STOP
objects.text: Same as Force Stasis but applied to any inert or living object around you, within a radius of ten to twenty metres, giving the impression that time has stopped completely. Cannot be maintained for more than one minute.

rows.title: TRAINING EVENTS
rows.titleText:
Sometimes you think back to your youth and the adventures you had during your training. All memories are precious, the good ones as well as the bad ones. What are your most intense memories and how did they shape you?

Pick up to three Memories and a Conclusion for each.

objects.title: FORBIDDEN LOVE
objects.text: Many people think the Sith can't love. That's not true. They can, and yet most refrain, wary of the inherent vulnerability. You had a forbidden and sulfurous love affair during your training - with someone you met on a planet during a mission, perhaps, or another Sich apprentice... Perhaps even a Jedi Padawan?

objects.title: CAMP-FIRE TALK
objects.text:
A curious shiver runs through you when you think back to that strange evening on a distant planet as you camped around a fire beside your Master. They started a conversation with you, infused with a humanity and sincerity that is rare in a Sith Lord, which has marked you forever. 

What did he talk to you about that night?

objects.title: THE WANDERING SENTINEL
objects.text:
You will remember all your life the disastrous mission that your Master sent you to accomplish. You were tracked and intercepted, far from all possible help, by a Jedi Shadow - a Jedi Sentinel dedicated to the eradication of the Sith and their followers - and their men. 

How did you survive?

objects.title: A Well-Kept Secret
objects.text: Both of you have managed to keep your relationship a secret and continue to date each other in short but intense reunions. Do you still see each other?
objects.deactivateThisChoice: Path of Solitude,Caught in the Act

objects.title: The Confession
objects.text: Your Master told you about themself, lifting for you the veil on his past and revealing to you a hidden side of their personality. You never looked at them the same way again afterwards.

objects.title: A Sinister Scar
objects.text: You fought valiantly and miraculously managed to escape from them, but not without them leaving a scar on your body and the promise of one day finding you to end this story.

objects.title: Caught in the Act
objects.text: Your Master surprised you both when you thought you were alone. But what happen afterwards? Did your Master force you to kill them, or did they use your attachment as a shackle?

objects.title: The Tale
objects.text: Your Master shared with you that night a forgotten, even hidden, part of Sith history and taught you things that no Apprentice is supposed to know.

objects.title: The Merciful Jedi
objects.text: They had you at their mercy, lightsaber ready to decapitate you... But at the last second they turned away and simply ordered you to get out of their sight. A sign of compassion towards a child ?

objects.title: Path of Solitude
objects.text: You yourself severed all bonds with them, despite their pleas. From now on, only the Dark Side matters to you, and you don't need anyone else - only the Force.
objects.deactivateThisChoice: A Well-Kept Secret,Caught in the Act

objects.title: The Legacy
objects.text: Your Master transmitted to you, that night, an ancestral technique that they had learned from their own Master. You vowed to pass it on to your future apprentice in due course.

objects.title: Last-Minute Rescue
objects.text: Later, you understood that it was a trap from the start. You were only a bait to lure out the Jedi - who didn't sense your Master coming to unleash hell on them.

objects.title: SURVIVAL
objects.text: You still remember that damn feral planet you spent months on. A treacherous jungle spreading as far as the eye can see - full of deadly danger. How did you end up there? Did your Master send you there on a mission, or did your ship just crash there by accident? There, you experienced something that changed you fundamentally.

objects.title: THE RIVAL
objects.text: Sometimes you think back to the first time you met the one who became your Rival. Who were they? Another Sith Lord's apprentice? A Jedi Padawan on a mission? A bounty hunter? You don't really remember what caused this rivalry between the two of you, but you know that it is not going to end anytime soon. How has this rivalry evolved today?

objects.title: GHOST FROM THE PAST
objects.text:
It was in a filthy cantina, in a half-ruined station, that your paths crossed again. A face you had long forgotten, from your past life, appeared before you. Was it an old friend? A relative, perhaps ? An influential person in your youth, like a mentor or a teacher, before you met your Master?

What happened then?

objects.title: Living God
objects.text: You met a tribe of natives and spent a few weeks among them, considered a living god. They taught you secrets about the force unknown even to the Sith.

objects.title: Healthy Rivalry
objects.text: You don't know if they are your friend or your rival. This ambiguous relationship is a mixture of respect, admiration, and a certain jealousy of the other's talents.

objects.title: Have a Drink, Pal
objects.text: You talked for hours over a drink about the past, about the good times, about what won't happen again. Then you said goodbye, aware that your paths were too far apart now to cross again.

objects.title: Rule of Strength
objects.text: You managed to survive on your own in this hell, and when you managed to escape from it, you emerged stronger, tougher, and more tenacious.

objects.title: Fierce Rivalry
objects.text: It pains you to admit it, but the bastard's good. Of course, you'll never accept that they're stronger than you. Equal? Perhaps. Not for long, of course.

objects.title: Silence
objects.text: You looked at each other in silence for a long time, painfully aware that you no longer had anything in common. Turning your back on them was hard, but you had to.
objects.deactivateThisChoice: Have a Drink Pal,Sever the Ties

objects.title: The Mentor
objects.text: You found on this planet an exiled old Sith, living as a hermit. You managed to gain their respect and learned various lightsaber techniques from them that were totally unknown to you.

objects.title: Hostile Rivalry
objects.text: They're less your rival than your Nemesis. You've fought each other many times. But no one's been able to kill the other one yet. Death, however, is the only thing that can bring an end to your long-standing conflict

objects.title: Sever the Ties
objects.text: You couldn't leave behind you anything that connected you to your past - A Sith has no past. Your lightsaber spoke for you and erased a face from your memory.

objects.title: THE HOLOCRON
objects.text: As a part of your training, your Master once handed you a strange, dusty old holocron and locked you in a room with the device, with only the instruction to discuss with the intelligence inhabiting it. And that's what you did, wary but curious. What kind of information was stored in that holocron?

objects.title: BAPTISM OF FIRE
objects.text: To lead men into battle is never easy. That day was your best med member it for the rest of your life. Your Master had placed a squad of soldiers under your command and sent you to the battlefield to eliminate some of their enemies, entrenched in a fortress. What struck you most that day, as you advanced under the continuous fire of the opposing camp?

objects.title: THE LIGHTSABER
objects.text: As you look at your Lightsaber, you can't help but recall the unconventional way you acquired it and the adventures that followed. It has its own history and is just as unique as the Sith who wields it. So, under what circumstances did you obtain your lightsaber, or rather... under what circumstances did it choose you?

objects.title: The Fallen
objects.text: It was the datatron of a dark Jedi. They taught you many things about the Jedi Order, its weaknesses and its darkest aspects, giving you a distinct advantage.

objects.title: The Horror of War
objects.text: The smell of blood, the sight of charred corpses, the screams of agony... That day was a milestone in your training and toughened you up considerably against the violence of the galaxy.

objects.title: The Champion
objects.text: How you ended up as a gladiator in the arena of Besberra one day would be too long a story. What matters is that you took your saber from the champion's corpse, after killing them with a knife.

objects.title: The Founder
objects.text: It was the datacron of one of the earliest Sith Lords. The knowledge of the Force and the Dark Side they delivered to you is priceless.

objects.title: The Ecstasy of Battle
objects.text: The adrenaline rushing to your brain, the hissing of blaster shots in your ears, the danger. What a day. After that battle, you knew you had found your true calling.

objects.title: The Game
objects.text: As improbable as it may seem, you won it in a game of dice... against a prince of royal blood, in a ship slowly drifting towards a black hole. And you were drunk.

objects.title: The Entity
objects.text: Whatever came out of the holocron was an obscure, shapeless thing. It shared many disturbing teachings about the universe itself, the fabric of reality and your own destiny.

objects.title: The Sorrow
objects.text: You lost many soldiers that day. Your soldiers. They say the Sith have no feelings. Well, you decided after that battle that you would be the first to care for the lives of your men, from now.
objects.deactivateThisChoice: The Horror of War,The Ecstasy of Battle

objects.title: The Treasure
objects.text: You found it, buried under the sand on a beach, in a chest. You were guided by a strange voice resonating in your mind. To this day, you're convinced it was the lightsaber itself.

objects.title: SITH TRIAL
objects.text:
One day, your Master decided to test you by presenting you with a particularly arduous challenge, on a isolated planet, designed to test a specific aspect essential to a Sith. You still have a cold sweat as you look back on that day and the unlikely way you came through it. 

What exactly was your Master trying to test?

objects.title: FIRST KILL
objects.text:
The first kill may be traumatic for some Sith, but it is a necessary step to detach oneself from one's humanity and begin one's true progression into the dark side of the Force. It is not uncommon for a Sith Master to script the very first murder committed by their apprentice to make the moment even more impactful. 

Who were you tasked to kill?

objects.title: THE ZIGGURAT
objects.text: How you discovered this temple would be an interesting story in itself. Were you on a mission for your Master? Were you lost on a planet that once belonged to the Sith in ancient and forgotten times? Or was the entire journey just a dream induced by the dark side of the Force? Either way, you found something very valuable in that place.

objects.title: Your Might
objects.text: You were dropped in a desert, deprived of your Lightsaber, and had to face an incredibly dangerous beast head-on, with a rudimentary and unsuitable weapon.

objects.title: Thugs
objects.text: There were three of them, and they were armed. You were not. Your Master ordered them to kill you and warned you that they would not help you. You're still alive. They're not.

objects.title: Yourself
objects.text: As aberrant as it may seem, it was you yourself who you encountered in this temple and who you fought, with your sword and with the Force. The result of this duel? You tell me.

objects.title: Your Grit
objects.text: You were instructed to brave a blizzard and climb a huge mountain with your bare hands to pick a flower growing exclusively at the top.

objects.title: Innocents
objects.text: A couple of civilians that your Master had randomly kidnapped from some village. "Kill them" they told you in a cold voice. A disciple obeys their Master.

objects.title: The Fountain
objects.text: The water flowing in it was black as ink. You took a sip and it was enough to permeate your very soul. It was pure Force, in liquid form. An incredible power passed through your veins.

objects.title: Your Wit
objects.text: You had to go through a very ancient underground maze, filled with strange puzzles and cryptic riddles. One tiny mistake was all it took to trigger deadly traps.

objects.title: Nobility
objects.text: Breaking into the heavily guarded villa was a challenge in itself. Assassinating them in their bed without waking their spouse was a real feat. Escape, chased by the security force? You don't even know how you did it.

objects.title: An Answer
objects.text: You do not know how you managed to decipher the runes covering the inner walls of the temple, but they revealed a dark secret about yourself.

rows.id: AND SO, THE STUDENT BECAME THE MASTER...
rows.title: AND SO, THE STUDENT BECAME THE MASTER...
rows.titleText:
Two there should be. No more, no less. One to embody power, the other to crave it. But to keep alive the Sith lineage, the apprentice has to slay the master to gain the title and take on their own disciple. The day you killed your Master is perhaps the most vivid and the most burning of all your memories. The day you became a Sith Lord... 
How did it happen? 
Pick a Memory

objects.title: EPIC DUEL
objects.text: When the time came, you simply challenged your Master properly. You faced each other, silent for a few seconds, leading to an incredible duel at the end of which you surpassed your Master and killed them. In their eyes, you saw that they died knowing that their legacy was in good hands.

objects.title: ASSASSINATION
objects.text: You murdered your Master when they least expected it. Perhaps you killed them in their bed while they slept, hid a bomb in their ship, or poured poison into their glass during a meal. Either way, they died without a fight, perhaps never knowing of your treachery. After all, isn't that the way of the Sith?

objects.title: SURPRISE ATTACK
objects.text: Naive master... Too sure of themself. They lowered their guard when they shouldn't have and you took the opportunity to jump on and backstab them, slashing them with your lightsaber. Cursing you, coughing blood, they tried to defend themself after that but it was too late. Their agonized end was not pretty to see.

objects.title: IT'S A TRAP!
objects.text: You devised a strategy to lure your Master into a trap from which they would have no chance to escape. Perhaps you gave the Jedi Order their geographic coordinates so they could set up an ambush? Either way, they was killed by their enemies while you watched your work from a distance, satisfied.

objects.title: LEFT FOR DEAD
objects.text: It was right after a battle, or a fight against their enemies. Halfdead, bloody, heavily injured, they crawled to you and asked for help. You gave them nothing but a look of disdain and a whisper: "I see only weakness." You then turned your back on them, abandoning them to their fate. To this day, you don't know if they survived this betrayal or not.

objects.title: VANISHED
objects.text: Actually, you didn't kill your Master. In fact, when you felt that you had nothing more to learn from them, you simply seized the first opportunity to escape from their vigilance, stole a spaceship and disappeared without a trace. Does your Master believe you are dead now, or are they still looking for you, somewhere?

rows.title: SITH LORD NAME
rows.titleText:
What is a Sith Lord without a proper name? You had to adopt one after leaving the teachings of your Master. What is it? You are Darth...

Roll 3d20 to now your Sith Lord name, the first die for the first syllable, the second one for the intermediary letter, and the third one for the last syllable.

rows.title: WHEN YOU LOOK AT THE DARK SIDE, CAREFUL YOU MUST BE, FOR THE DARK SIDE LOOKS BACK.
